            <ol>
                <li>1. Add 1 x Crisis Trap Class Chaos Card for each Player + 1 extra to the Deck before initial Shuffling and Dealing [01.1].</li>
                <li>2. Choose a Special Victory Condition before starting [01.1].</li>
            </ol>
            
            <h3>FUNCTIONS OF THE CRISIS EXPANSION’S TRAP CLASS CHAOS CARDS:</h3>
            <div class="note-box">
                <strong>NOTE:</strong> All Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards are placed in front of the Player that Revealed It; they are NOT Shuffled back into the Deck [01.1].
            </div>

            <h3>• SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITION NOTES:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>a. Light, the Rule of the Few:</strong> If all Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards are in play, the game ends and the Player/s with the least amount of them [including NOT having any] Win/Draw [01.1].</li>
                <li><strong>b. Harmony, the Rule of Balance:</strong> Alternating each game:
                    <ul>
                        <li>i. Speed, Rule of the First: The first Player to Reveal a Crisis Trap Class Chaos Card instantly Wins [01.1].</li>
                        <li>ii. Survival, Rule of the Last: One by one, each Player Revealing a Crisis Trap Class Chaos Card instantly loses. The last Player without one, Wins [01.1].</li>
                    </ul>
                    <div class="note-box">
                        <strong>2 PLAYER GAME NOTE:</strong> This is the best Special Victory Condition for a 2 Player Game. Just add a single Crisis Trap Class Chaos Card to the Deck. Or while 2 Players are left due to others having been removed from the game, just count the next one to be Revealed [01.1].
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li><strong>c. Dark, the Rule of the Many:</strong> Once a Player Reveals Their 2nd Crisis Trap Class Chaos Card, the game ends automatically and that Player Wins [01.1].</li>
                <li><strong>d. Chaos, the Rule of the Impartial:</strong> Simply a Game Timer. If all Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards are in play, the game ends with no clear Winner [see: (01-A) Soloverse - Crazy 8’s (Game Rulebook): Victory Conditions: Rule 5] [01.1].</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="note-box">
                <strong>VARIATION:</strong> You CAN always alter the number of copies to change Game Time [01.1].
            </div>
            <div class="note-box">
                <strong>NOTE:</strong> If playing with other Expansions that Remove Players from the Game, any Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards Removed Players have accumulated beforehand will still count towards these Victory Conditions [so even if You have been eliminated, You may still have a chance to Win] [01.1].
            </div>
        </div>
